# String interpolation

R.2 lowers `s"prefix ${expr} suffix"` to Rust's `format!("prefix {} suffix", expr)`.

```scalascript
def greeting(name: String, age: Long): String =
  s"Hello, $name — age $age"

@main def run(): Unit =
  println(greeting("Sergiy", 42))
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust string-interp.ssc
./string-interp                # → Hello, Sergiy — age 42
```
